  "prompt": "Where can I update the latest FIFA squad 14 for PC offline?",
  "response": "Updating the squad data for FIFA 14 on PC can be done using community-made patches and mods, as official support for FIFA 14 has long been discontinued. Here\u2019s a general guide on how you can do this:\n\n1. **Find a Reliable Modding Community**: Search for FIFA 14 mods on platforms like ModdingWay, Soccergaming, or dedicated forums where the community shares their patches. These websites often host updated rosters and other mods for various iterations of FIFA.\n\n2. **Download the Update**: Once you\u2019ve found a trustworthy source, download the squad update files. These usually come in a format compatible with FIFA 14\u2019s file structure.\n\n3. **Backup Original Files**: Before making any changes, it's crucial to backup your original FIFA 14 files. This ensures you can restore your game in case something goes wrong during the modding process.\n\n4. **Install the Mod**: Follow the instructions provided with the update. This often involves copying and replacing specific files in the FIFA 14 game directory. Pay attention to the instructions regarding file locations and any additional tools you might need.\n\n5. **Check for Additional Tools**: Sometimes, mods require additional software like an updated version of Creation Master, which can help with complex mod installations.\n\n6. **Launch the Game**: After installation, launch FIFA 14 and check the rosters to ensure that they have been updated as expected.\n\nRemember to always download mods from reputable sources to avoid any security risks. Additionally, participating in the forums or community discussions can provide further support if you encounter issues during the update process.",
